        "text": "The document page is from the New York ISO Aggregation Manual and includes a table of contents for sections 5 to 7. Here's a summary:\n\n### Section 5: Transmission Nodes\n- **5.1**: Discusses member system topology considerations and the active transmission node list.\n- **5.2**: Covers transmission node changes, including the change timeline.\n- **5.3**: Details DER (Distributed Energy Resource) designation to a transmission node and related changes.\n- **5.4**: Focuses on transmission node operations.\n- **5.5**: Outlines aggregator responsibilities.\n\n### Section 6: Operational Coordination\n- **6.1**: Describes operating data exchange, including planned and unplanned system maintenance, market bids, outage reporting, and dispatch instructions.\n- **6.2**: Defines roles and responsibilities, emphasizing communication between various entities like distribution utilities, transmission owners, aggregators, and NYISO.\n- **6.3**: Provides a coordination timeline for dispatch activities, detailing specific timeframes for actions before and after dispatch.\n\n### Section 7: Metering & Telemetry\n- **7.1**: Offers background information.\n- **7.2**: Lists metering requirements.\n- **7.3**: Details telemetry requirements, including a specific telemetry testing procedure for NYISO-member systems.\n\nThis page outlines the structure and key topics covered in these sections of the manual.",
