        "text": "The document page is from the New York ISO Aggregation Manual and provides guidance for market participants on contacting NYISO for support with unusual DMNC (Dependable Maximum Net Capability) submission scenarios. It outlines three specific scenarios where contact is necessary:\n\n1. **Single Resource Type ESR Aggregation**: \n   - For aggregations with only electrochemical batteries requiring a 1-hour DMNC duration test.\n   - Aggregators must contact NYISO after submitting to the Aggregation System for review and support.\n   - If the aggregation has an EDL (Effective Duration Limit), it must meet the EDL testing requirement.\n\n2. **Existing Stand-alone Generator Transition**:\n   - For DMNC records of existing generators with a valid DMNC test transitioning to an SRT (Stand-alone Resource Type) Aggregation with an EDL.\n   - Aggregators must contact NYISO for guidance on submitting both prior-approved and current DMNC tests.\n   - Additional information is available in specific sections of the ICAP Manual.\n\n3. **DER Facility Changing Aggregations**:\n   - For DER facilities changing to another aggregation with different DMNC test hours.\n   - Facilities may carry over an existing DMNC value if changing to an aggregation with an EDL that is less than or equal to the former EDL, or if changing to a longer EDL with time stacking.\n\nThe document provides references to specific sections of the ICAP Manual for further details.",
