        "score": 0.5654079,
        "text": "The document page contains recommendations related to the New York Independent System Operator (NYISO) and its operations:\n\n1. **Efficient Pricing and Settlement for Congestion Relief (High Priority)**:\n   - NYISO should consider rules for efficient pricing and settlement when operating reserve providers help manage congestion.\n   - The current system does not compensate these providers adequately, leading to inefficient investment signals.\n   - The recommendation is crucial due to New York City's expected loss of up to 1300 MW of peaking generation over the next five years.\n   - Proper compensation for reserve providers is necessary to encourage investment in resources with flexible characteristics.\n\n2. **Eliminate Transaction Fees for CTS at the PJM-NYISO Border**:\n   - The Coordinated Transaction Scheduling (CTS) process with PJM has not met expectations since its implementation in 2014.\n   - Utilization of CTS at the ISO-NE interface is higher due to the absence of transaction fees.\n   - The recommendation suggests eliminating fees to improve the effectiveness of CTS with PJM, as current fees and uplift charges hinder its functionality.",
