rrent[FERC] pro forma standards for queue process and management. Reform proposals are specific to the ISO or RTO and often include greater financial deposits or full demonstration of site control from interconnection customers to enter the queue (first-ready, ... The[FERC] has taken notice of the backlog issue and has directed RTOs and ISOs to report on the status of their efforts to improve the processing of their interconnection queues. RTOs and ISOs have identified the two biggest problems with the original interconnection requirements as the ease of entry into the interconnection queues and the serial study approach. Many transmission providers are increasing the deposit amount to enter the queue as well as requiring the applicant to meet certain milestones such as power ... tightening their requirements for allowing generating projects to suspend their interconnection requests. Interconnection queues and study processes vary from region to region. Below are some of the reforms the various RTOs"
